value.value: A molecular function that controls the rate, timing and/or magnitude of gene transcription. The function of transcriptional regulators is to modulate gene expression at the transcription step so that they are expressed in the right cell at the right time and in the right amount throughout the life of the cell and the organism. Genes are transcriptional units, and include bacterial operons.
Catalyzes the activation of choline trimethylamine-lyase by generation of an organic free radical on a glycine residue via a homolytic cleavage of S-adenosyl-L-methionine (SAM).

The assembly and secretion a set of components to form an extracellular vesicule, a membrane-bounded vesicle that is released into the extracellular region. Extracellular vesicles include exosomes, microvesicles and apoptotic bodies, based on the mechanism by which they are released from cells and differentiated based on their size and content.
The assembly and secretion of a set of components to form an extracellular microvesicule, a membrane-bounded vesicle that ranges in size 100 nm to 1 micron in size) and exits the cell by budding.

Any process carried out at the cellular level that reduces or removes the toxicity of a fluoride. These may include chemical modification or transport of fluoride away from sensitive areas and to compartments or complexes whose purpose is sequestration of the toxic substance.
The directed movement of some substance from inside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the extracellular region.
The directed movement of fluoride ions from inside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the extracellular region.
The aggregation, arrangement and bonding together of a set of components to form a Lewy body.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of Lewy body formation.

label.value: negative regulation of Lewy body formation

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of Lewy body formation.

label.value: positive regulation of Lewy body formation

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of Lewy body formation.
The directed movement of thiamine from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of lymphocyte chemotaxis.
Binding to an iron-sulfur cluster and delivering it to an acceptor molecule.

label.value: symbiont-mediated suppression of host cytokine production

value.value: A process by which a symbiont inhibits or disrupts cytokine production in the host organism. The host is defined as the larger of the organisms involved in a symbiotic interaction.
Enables the transmembrane transfer of a monoatomic cation by a channel that opens in response to a mechanical stress.
The process in which a guanine nucleotide is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
The process in which a potassium ion is transported across a mitochondrial membrane, into or out of the mitochondrion.
Binding to and carrying a cargo between the nucleus and the cytoplasm by moving along with the cargo. The cargo can be either a RNA or a protein.
The directed movement of copper ions out of the vacuole across the vacuolar membrane.
The directed movement of calcium cations into the vacuole across the vacuolar membrane.
The directed movement of zinc ions from inside the vacuole across the vacuolar membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of an ammonium ion from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of borate from inside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the extracellular region.
Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: monocarboxylate(out) + Na+(out) = monocarboxylate(in) + Na+(in).
Binding to a Golgi transport complex, a multisubunit tethering complex of the CATCHR family.

label.value: positive regulation of adenylate cyclase-activating adrenergic receptor signaling pathway involved in heart process

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of an adenylate cyclase-activating adrenergic receptor signaling pathway involved in some heart process.

label.value: negative regulation of adenylate cyclase-activating adrenergic receptor signaling pathway involved in heart process

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of an adenylate cyclase-activating adrenergic receptor signaling pathway involved in some heart process.
The directed movement of urea from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of a polyamine from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of spermidine from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of pyridoxal from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of an oligopeptide from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of a dipeptide from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
The directed movement of a tripeptide from outside of a cell, across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

label.value: apoptotic process in response to mitochondrial fragmentation

value.value: Any apoptotic process that occurs as a result of mitochondrial fragmentation.

label.value: zinc ion import into endoplasmic reticulum

value.value: The directed import of zinc(2+) from the cytosol, across the endoplasmic reticulum membrane, into the endoplasmic reticulum.

definition.value: This term covers zinc(2+) import *across* the endoplasmic reticulum membrane through a channel or pore. It does not cover import via vesicle fusion with endoplasmic reticulum membrane, as in this case transport does not involve crossing the membrane.

label.value: protein transport along microtubule to kinetochore

value.value: Any process in which a protein is transported to the kinetochore along a microtubule.

Enables the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction: folic acid(out) + H+(out) = folic acid(in) + H+(in). The main folic acid symporter is the Proton-Coupled Folate Transporter (PCFT/SLC46A1), which has similar affinity for transport of reduced folates (5-methyl THF, 5-formyl THF) and folic acid.

label.value: regulation of long-chain fatty acid import into cell

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of long-chain fatty acid import into a cell.

label.value: negative regulation of long-chain fatty acid import into cell

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of long-chain fatty acid import into a cell.

label.value: positive regulation of long-chain fatty acid import into cell

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of long-chain fatty acid import into a cell.

label.value: regulation of D-aspartate import across plasma membrane

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the directed import of D-aspartate from the extracellular region across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

label.value: negative regulation of D-aspartate import across plasma membrane

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the directed import of D-aspartate from the extracellular region across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.

label.value: positive regulation of D-aspartate import across plasma membrane

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the directed import of D-aspartate from the extracellular region across the plasma membrane and into the cytosol.
A membrane-bound intracellular compartment that is formed upon internalization of a pathogen into a host cell, and in which the pathogen resides.
Host-derived membrane of a pathogen-containing vacuole.
The enclosed volume within the sealed membrane of a pathogen-containing vacuole.

A molecular function required for core promoter activity that mediates the assembly of the RNA polymerase holoenzyme at promoter DNA to form the pre-initiation complex (PIC). General transcription factors (GTFs) bind to and open promoter DNA, initiate RNA synthesis and stimulate the escape of the polymerase from the promoter. Not all subunits of the general transcription factor are necessarily present at all promoters to initiate transcription. GTFs act at each promoter, although the exact subunit composition at individual promoters may vary.

definition.value: Usage guidance: The distinction between general transcription factors and DNA-binding transcription factors is that the latter modulate the selection of which genes are expressed under specific conditions, while general transcription factors are the constitutive machinery required for transcription initiation.

value.value: A protein complex that regulates Arp2/3 complex-mediated actin nucleation.
